etter reden. Roland Barthes über Klima, Alltäglichkeit, Seinsgefühl und Poetik -- tÜber die Autorinnen und Autoren -- tRegister0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDer Band deckt literarische Thematisierungsweisen des Wetters auf. Diese erfüllen eine Vielzahl von Funktionen, die über reine Staffage und Effekt hinausführen. Der komparatistische Zugang entwickelt möglichst verallgemeinerbare Kategorien zu ästhetischer Praxis sowie poetologischer Reflexion und trägt den Entwicklungen in unterschiedlichen Literaturen Rechnung.  aThis volume examines how the weather is addressed in literature, covering a range of functions that go beyond mere decoration and effect. Its comparative approach develops categories of aesthetic practice and poetological reflection that are as representative as possible and does justice to developments in various literatures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aDarstellungsverfahren. 4aKlima. 4aLiteratur. 4aPoetologie. 4aWetter. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aWeather.  aclimate.  aliterature.  amodes of presentation.  apoetology.1 aAttanucci, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüttner, Urs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüttner, Urs, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDirschauer, Marlene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurham Peters, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGamper, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGamper, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGisbertz, Anna-Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ct